ro rosso’s annual wine guide drops the italian wine world stops as winemakers scan the influential italian magazine’s list to check their fortunes badia di morrona chianti i sodi del paretaio is a perennial gambero favorite having earned multiple “due bicchieri” “two glasses” honors in addition to praise as a “sincere wonderfully drinkable wine” the wine access clients who have stocked their cellars with past vintages of this “especially good value” with “exceptional breadth on the nose” couldn’t agree more and they’ll be first to claim this gem from the excellent  vintage by the case the land of badia di morrona in the picturesque hills between florence and pisa was first worked by th century benedictine monks today it is owned by count gaslini alberti who has invested a fortune in the winery over the past  years outfitting winemaker corrado dal piaz with a refurbished facility enlarged cellars and new casks and barrels dal piaz is notoriously hard on the badia’s  acres of grapes which soak up the sun on south and southeastern exposed slopes strewn with chunks of white limestone he tightened spacing in the vines orchestrating a darwinian competition that leads to tiny berries of high skintojuice ratio the result is sangiovese of great richness and phenolic complexity ’s long growing season allowed temperamental sangiovese to reach rare almost perfectly uniform maturity the vines stretched deep underground sucking up the mineral imprint of the poor soil putting out a dark crushedredfruit sangiovese infused with garrigue and bracketed by perfectly ripe tannins if you’re looking for vibrancy in your topclass chianti you’ll be hardpressed to find anything quite like this luscious  at  and as gambero rosso would advise this is one to be opened — and a case to be bought — without hesitation tasting notes wineaccess travel log the  badia di morrona chianti i sodi del paretaio is bright ruby to the edge with a fabulous nose of wild berry blue flower and tangy spices juicy and hightoned on the attack with sneaky weight and supple texture this is textbook chianti wine facts type red wine varietal sangiovese country italy region tuscany appellation chianti docg alcohol by volume    bottles   bottles   bottles by law this offer may only be shipped to the following states ak az ca co ct dc fl ga hi ia id il in ks la ma me mn mo mt nc nd ne nh nm nv oh or pa sc tn va vt wa wi wv wy shipping included offer does not apply to shipments to hawaii and alaska the world’s finest wines direct from the source we curate exclusive wines from every region cutting out the middlemen to bring you the best prices simple enough get access great wine is made with extraordinary optimism and grapes winemaking like anything else worth doing requires you trust your instincts and take some risks we take the risk out of finding extraordinary wines but none of the adventure shop our wines featured in the store extraordinary vintages handselected by our experts and ready to ship today bold — opulent — red  teeter totter cabernet sauvignon napa valley  btl the  teetertotter cabernet boasts the fingerprints of a master craftsman bold and dark rubypurple in the glass bursting with classic cabernet notes of blackcurrant mocha anise and subtle toasty notes framed by new wood cedar full bodied boasting silky black fruit alluring earthy notes and purple florals a rich and lingering finish is braced by finegrained tannins enjoy now for its opulent youthful blackfruited purity or cellar for at least a decade — wine access member rating get the full story featured in the store extraordinary vintages handselected by our experts and ready to ship today bold — opulent — red  teeter totter cabernet sauvignon napa valley  btl the  teetertotter cabernet boasts the fingerprints of a master craftsman bold and dark rubypurple in the glass bursting with classic cabernet notes of blackcurrant mocha anise and subtle toasty notes framed by new wood cedar full bodied boasting silky black 